It was a sad day for CANSA Lowveld as they lost their beloved, Sr Rona Labuschagne on Thursday. During the CANSA Shades of Pink Walk at Emnotweni Southern Sun, they had a moment of silence in remembrance of her life and the role she played in the community. Labuschagne retired from CANSA last year after over 34 years of service. WATCH:  ALSO READ: Sr Rona retires from CANSA Read more in the next publication of Lowvelder. ALSO READ: Myths vs facts on breast cancer